               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18770305-name-339" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18770305-name-339" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770305-name-339" type="surname" value="BARTLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770305-name-339" type="given" value="SIDNEY"></interp>SIDNEY BARTLE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a clerk—I live at 451, Old Kent Road—on 17th February I was on Tower Hill—there was a crowd there—I felt my chain fall down and saw the prisoner running—I ran after him, tapped him on</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="187703050081"></xptr>
               <p>the shoulder, and said "Give me my chain"—he said "I have not got it, I will give you something," and I saw him hand my watch to another person—I gave the prisoner in charge—my watch was not found—it was worth 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined.</hi> My watch was in my waistcoat pocket, and my coat was fastened by one button, and the chain was showing—I swear positively that I saw the watch in the prisoner's hand—he held it out in this way and I saw it passed on.</p>
               <p>----Peek (<hi rend="italic">Policeman H</hi> 176). I was called and found the prisoner detained—he was charged with stealing the watch—he said that he had not'</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined.</hi> He said "I have not got the watch; I have not seen the watch; I have only just come up."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">The Prisoners Statement before the Magistrate:</hi> "He tapped me on the shoulder and said 'Give me my watch?' I said 'What watch, I have not got any watch? search me.' I never ran away."</p>
